QuickBite AWS EC2 + GitHub Actions CI/CD Guide (Hinglish)

0) Overview
- Backend Java 21 LTS aur frontend Node 24 LTS par build hota hai.
- Docker images GHCR (GitHub Container Registry) me push honge.
- EC2 par docker-compose se services run hongi.

1) AWS EC2 Setup (Ubuntu 22.04 LTS recommended)
1.1) EC2 instance launch karo
- Instance: t3.large ya usse upar (microservices + MySQL + Kafka ke liye)
- Storage: 30-50 GB
- Key pair: naya ya existing (.pem)

1.2) Security Group rules (minimum)
- SSH: 22 (source: your IP)
- HTTP: 80 (0.0.0.0/0)
- HTTPS: 443 (0.0.0.0/0)
- Optional (sirf test/debug ke liye):
  - 9090 (API Gateway)
  - 8761 (Eureka dashboard)
  - 3000 (Frontend if mapped)

1.3) EC2 par login
- Windows PowerShell example:
  ssh -i "C:\path\to\key.pem" ubuntu@EC2_PUBLIC_IP

2) EC2 par Docker aur Compose install karo
2.1) Packages update
- sudo apt-get update

sdfghj

2.2) Docker Engine install
- sudo apt-get install -y ca-certificates curl gnupg
- sudo install -m 0755 -d /etc/apt/keyrings
- curl -fsSL https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu/gpg | sudo gpg --dearmor -o /etc/apt/keyrings/docker.gpg
- sudo chmod a+r /etc/apt/keyrings/docker.gpg
- echo "deb [arch=$(dpkg --print-architecture) signed-by=/etc/apt/keyrings/docker.gpg] https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu $(. /etc/os-release && echo $VERSION_CODENAME) stable" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/docker.list > /dev/null
- sudo apt-get update
- sudo apt-get install -y docker-ce docker-ce-cli containerd.io docker-buildx-plugin docker-compose-plugin

2.3) Docker group permissions
- sudo usermod -aG docker $USER
- newgrp docker

3) Repo clone aur secrets set karo
3.1) Code clone
- sudo mkdir -p /opt/quickbite
- sudo chown $USER:$USER /opt/quickbite
- cd /opt/quickbite
- git clone <YOUR_GITHUB_REPO_URL> .

3.2) Production env values
- Real secrets set karo:
  - JWT_SECRET
  - GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID
  - GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET
  - RAZORPAY_KEY_ID
  - RAZORPAY_KEY_SECRET
- Recommended: docker-compose.prod.yml banao jisme env vars real ho.

Example docker-compose.prod.yml (idea only):
- image: ghcr.io/<owner>/<repo>/api-gateway:latest
- build: removed
- environment: real secrets

3.3) GHCR login (EC2)
- docker login ghcr.io -u <GITHUB_USERNAME>
- Password: PAT with read:packages

4) Docker compose run (EC2)
4.1) Images pull
- docker compose -f docker-compose.yml -f docker-compose.prod.yml pull

4.2) Start services
- docker compose -f docker-compose.yml -f docker-compose.prod.yml up -d

4.3) Status check
- docker compose ps
- docker compose logs -f api-gateway

5) GitHub Actions CI/CD setup
5.1) Repo me already workflow hai: .github/workflows/ci-cd.yml
- Java 21 aur Node 24 ke sath tests/run hota hai
- Docker images GHCR par push hoti hain (main/master)

5.2) Required GitHub Secrets for deploy (agar auto deploy chahiye)
- EC2_HOST
- EC2_USER
- EC2_SSH_KEY (private key contents)
- EC2_SSH_PORT (optional, default 22)

5.3) Deploy job (high-level idea)
- Build + push ke baad SSH se EC2 par:
  - cd /opt/quickbite
  - git pull (optional)
  - docker login ghcr.io
  - docker compose pull
  - docker compose up -d

6) Production tips
- RDS MySQL use karna better rahega (MySQL container se avoid).
- Kafka ke liye managed MSK consider karo.
- JWT_SECRET ko strong random string banao.
- Backups aur log rotation plan karo.
- Domain chahiye to Nginx/ALB + SSL (ACM) use karo.

7) Quick verification URLs
- Frontend: http://EC2_PUBLIC_IP (ya domain)
- API Gateway: http://EC2_PUBLIC_IP:9090
- Eureka (optional): http://EC2_PUBLIC_IP:8761

Done. Agar chaho to main deploy job ka exact GitHub Actions snippet bhi add kar sakta hoon.